		<title><![CDATA[How to Update Your Mobile Number in Aadhar: A Detailed 2024 Guide for Easy Navigation]]></title>
		<link>https://thetechnologyfiction.com/blog/how-to-change-mobile-number-in-aadhar-a-step-by-step-guide-2024/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 06 Jan 2024 09:39:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Harshweb]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://thetechnologyfiction.com/?p=1250</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1 class="wp-block-heading">Aadhaar Card Updation</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Keeping your Aadhaar card information up-to-date is crucial, especially your mobile number. It's linked to various critical services and receives important updates. If you need to change your mobile number in Aadhaar, here's a comprehensive guide to help you through the process in India.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>1. Choose Your Update Method:</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>There are two ways to update your Aadhaar mobile number:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Offline:</strong> Visit a Permanent Enrolment Centre (PEC) or Aadhaar Seva Kendra (ASK). This is the recommended method if you haven't registered a mobile number yet or haven't updated it recently.<br></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":1251,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://uidai.gov.in/en/ecosystem/enrolment-ecosystem/aadhaar-seva-kendra.html"><img src="https://thetechnologyfiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/aadhar-seva-kenra-image.jpeg" alt="aadhar seva kendra image, How to Update Your Mobile Number in Aadhar" class="wp-image-1251"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Online:</strong> If you already have a registered mobile number linked to your Aadhaar, you can update you address and few other details as shown below,  through the UIDAI's Self Service Update Portal (SSUP) or from mobile you can use 'mAadhaar' App.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":1254,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://thetechnologyfiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-2-1024x621.png" alt="How to Update Your Mobile Number in Aadhar" class="wp-image-1254"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>2. Offline Update at PEC/ASK:</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Locate your nearest PEC or ASK. You can find them on the UIDAI website: <a href="https://appointments.uidai.gov.in/">https://appointments.uidai.gov.in/</a></h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Carry your Aadhaar card and a valid proof of address (POA) document, such as your driving license, voter ID, or bank statement.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Fill out the Aadhaar Data Update/Correction Form, selecting "Mobile Number" as the field you want to update.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Submit the form along with your Aadhaar card and POA document to the PEC/ASK representative.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 5:</strong> Provide your fingerprints and iris scan for biometric authentication.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 6:</strong> Pay the update fee of Rs. 50.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 7:</strong> You'll receive an update confirmation slip with a URN (Update Request Number). Keep this for future reference.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>3. Online Update via SSUP:</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":1255,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://thetechnologyfiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-3-1024x723.png" alt="" class="wp-image-1255"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Visit the UIDAI's Self Service Update Portal: <a href="https://myaadhaar.uidai.gov.in/">https://myaadhaar.uidai.gov.in/</a></h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Enter your aadhaar no and registered mobile no.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Enter the OTP received on your registered mobile number.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Select the what you want to update as shown in the above image and then click on "Proceed to Update Aadhaar Data."</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 5:</strong> Choose the field which your want to update.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 6:</strong> Enter your new value and confirm it.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 7:</strong> Upload a scanned copy of your valid POA document.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 8:</strong> Review your details and submit the update request.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 9:</strong> Pay the update fee of Rs. 50.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 10:</strong> You'll receive an update confirmation slip with a URN. Keep this for future reference.</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>4. Tracking Your Update:</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You can track the status of your update request using the URN on the UIDAI website: <a href="https://myaadhaar.uidai.gov.in/CheckAadhaarStatus">https://myaadhaar.uidai.gov.in/CheckAadhaarStatus</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Note: For Mobile Number update, you have to visit nearest Aadhar Seva Kendra only.</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>5. Receiving Your Updated Aadhaar:</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Your updated Aadhaar card with the new mobile number will be sent to your registered address within 60 days. You can also download the e-Aadhaar with the updated information from the UIDAI website.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Additional Tips:</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Ensure your new mobile number is active and accessible.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Keep your Aadhaar card and update confirmation slip safe.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Don't share your Aadhaar details or OTP with anyone.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>By following these steps, you can easily update your mobile number in Aadhaar and ensure your information remains accurate and secure. Remember, keeping your Aadhaar updated is essential for availing various government benefits and services.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br>In conclusion, updating your Aadhaar card is a straightforward process that ensures you stay connected to vital services and receive crucial updates. Whether you choose the offline method at a PEC/ASK or the online SSUP portal, following these steps guarantees a smooth update experience.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Remember, maintaining an accurate Aadhaar record is not only a regulatory requirement but also essential for accessing various government benefits and services seamlessly.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you've followed this guide, you're on the right track to having an updated Aadhaar card. Ensure you keep the update confirmation slip and the Aadhaar card in a secure place, and refrain from sharing sensitive information to safeguard your identity.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I hope this comprehensive guide with images and step-by-step instructions helps you navigate the Aadhaar mobile number update process with ease. You can contact me on my email id as given in the about section.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Check out more of my blogs by going to home page from <a href="https://thetechnologyfiction.com/">here</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->]]></content:encoded>
